UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 2578
1 A RESOLUTION recognizing the life of Charlie Kirk as a martyr for truth, faith,
2 and free speech.
3 WHEREAS, Charles James "Charlie" Kirk was born on October 14, 1993, in
4 Arlington Heights, Illinois, and was tragically assassinated on September 10, 2025; and
5 WHEREAS, though his life was cut short, Charlie Kirk became the preeminent
6 voice of a generation, inspiring millions of young Americans to engage in civic
7 discourse, champion conservative principles, and reclaim the foundational values of faith,
8 family, liberty, limited government, and individual responsibility; and
9 WHEREAS, in 2012, at age 18, Charlie Kirk co-founded and became the chief
10 executive officer of Turning Point USA, which began as a grassroots, shoestring campus
11 effort and was turned into a well-funded, highly effective national organization with
12 several affiliated groups, such as Turning Point Action and TPUSA Faith; and
13 WHEREAS, through his work and tireless advocacy at Turning Point USA, Charlie
14 Kirk led a transformative movement on college campuses and beyond, empowering
15 students to defend free markets, secure borders, and protect traditional family structures
16 against ideological overreach; and
17 WHEREAS, Charlie Kirk would become a widely known media figure around the
18 globe, hosting "The Charlie Kirk Show" on talk radio, appearing regularly on
19 conservative outlets, fostering an environment for open dialogue on America's college
20 campuses, and addressing such major political conferences as the 2024 Republican
21 National Convention and the 2022 Conservative Political Action Conference; and
22 WHEREAS, Charlie Kirk authored several books, including "Campus Battlefield"
23 in 2018, "The MAGA Doctrine" in 2020, "Right Wing Revolution" in 2024, and "Stop in
24 the Name of God" in 2025; and
25 WHEREAS, among his fans and admirers, Charlie Kirk earned a stellar reputation
26 for his skill as a debater and his continued focus on campus activism, youth engagement,
27 and faith-based organizing; and
Page 1 of 3
