UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 2578
1 WHEREAS, a vocal and unapologetic Christian, Charlie Kirk embodied the
2 Christian heritage that undergirds American exceptionalism, publicly proclaiming his
3 faith in Jesus Christ as a guiding force in the pursuit of justice, moral clarity, and defense
4 of the unborn; and
5 WHEREAS, Charlie Kirk's life was a testament to his profound Christian faith,
6 with him serving not only as a vocal beacon of spiritual conviction, but as a modern
7 politically conservative leader who wove the principles of truth, justice, and divine
8 purpose into the fabric of public civil discourse, inspiring countless souls to stand firm in
9 their beliefs amid a culture often hostile to conviction; and
10 WHEREAS, as a tireless free speech advocate, Charlie Kirk fought against
11 suppression by technology companies, university indoctrination, and government
12 overreach, ensuring that dissenting voices, especially those of the next generation, could
13 flourish in the public square, thereby preserving the First Amendment of the Constitution
14 of the United States as the bedrock of a free society; and
15 WHEREAS, through relentless persecution, cancellation attempts, smears, and his
16 ultimate assassination, Charlie Kirk became a martyr for truth and liberty, enduring
17 personal and professional attacks with an unwavering resolve to expose corruption,
18 challenge prevailing narratives, and uphold objective reality in the face of censorship and
19 cultural decay; and
20 WHEREAS, Charlie Kirk will be remembered for his many contributions to his
21 family, community, and nation, and will be deeply missed by all whose lives were
22 touched by his presence; and
23 WHEREAS, Charlie Kirk is survived by his beloved wife, Erika Frantzve Kirk, his
24 two beloved children, and a host of other family members, friends, and loved ones; and
25 WHEREAS, as a testament to Charlie Kirk's short but powerful tenure on this earth,
26 Kentuckians are encouraged on October 14, the date of his birth, to reflect on the
27 principles he championed, participate in educational events promoting civic engagement,
Page 2 of 3
XXXX 3/31/2026 1:20 PM Jacketed

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 2578
1 and honor his legacy as a martyr for truth and liberty;
2 NOW, THEREFORE,
3 Be it resolved by the Senate of the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of
4 Kentucky:
5 Section 1. The Senate acknowledges the extraordinary accomplishments of
6 Charlie Kirk and recognizes the cultural and political impact he leaves behind.
7 Section 2. The Senate commits in perpetuating Charlie Kirk's legacy by
8 upholding the freedoms he died defending, encouraging all Kentuckians to honor his
9 sacrifice through steadfast commitment to uphold our national values of liberty, truth, and
10 open discourse.
11 Section 3. The Clerk of the Senate is directed to transmit a copy of this
12 Resolution to Senator Lindsey Tichenor, Senator Steve Rawlings, and the board of
13 directors of Turning Point USA.
